## ğŸ¯ Objective

Enhance the security posture of the web application by:

- Addressing insecure coding practices from Week 1
- Validating and sanitizing all user inputs
- Implementing secure password hashing
- Ensuring proper session management
- Adding centralized logging for authentication events

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Key Security Measures Implemented

| Component        | Description                                                                 |
|------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| âœ… Input Validation | All user inputs sanitized using `validator` package                       |
| ğŸ” Password Security | Passwords hashed securely using `bcrypt`                                 |
| ğŸ§  Session Handling  | Session created only after successful login                              |
| ğŸ“ Logging System   | Custom logging using `fs` and `path`; records both success and failure   |
| ğŸ§ª Manual Testing   | Verified login/registration workflows with valid/invalid data             |

---

## ğŸ§ª Manual Test Results

| Action                                | Result                                      |
|---------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------|
| Login with valid credentials          | Session created, redirected to home         |
| Login with invalid credentials        | Access denied, log entry created            |
| Register with valid data              | Data stored, log entry created              |
| Attempt invalid input (XSS, script)   | Input rejected during validation            |

